The paper proposes a novel neural network model for joint part-of-speech tagging and dependency parsing, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The model also incorporates a BiLSTM-based tagging component, which is a popular technique in deep learning (DL) for NLP, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also reports state-of-the-art results on downstream tasks such as biomedical event extraction and opinion analysis, which could indicate relevance to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
